{
  "title": "Reading Folders",
  "source": "Reading Folders words.pdf (Montessori phonics material)",
  "markerConvention": {
    "syntax": "Target grapheme(s) wrapped in square brackets inside each word string.",
    "examples": {
      "b[ai]t": "b + <span class='sound'>ai</span> + t",
      "c[a]k[e]": "split digraph a-e -> highlight both 'a' and 'e'"
    },
    "html": "Split each word on /\\[([^\\]]+)\\]/; wrap captured groups in <span class=\"sound\"> (red). Strip brackets to get the plain word."
  },
  "legend": {
    "green": "key letter written on the folder cover",
    "red": "sound written on cards and word booklets",
    "blue": "key sound written on the back of each card"
  },
  "notes": [
    "Folders/graphemes follow the sound-family list in the PDF (ai, ee, ie, oa, ue, or, er, ou, oy, s, j, f, e, shun).",
    "Only words whose card grapheme is actually present are included, so every marker is valid. PDF words mis-filed under the wrong grapheme were dropped.",
    "Words are lowercased and de-duplicated per card.",
    "Several folders/cards are empty because the PDF listed no (usable) words for them (oa, or/au, er, ou, oy, cy, plain s, plain j, f, e, shun)."
  ],
